cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.GR 

The paper describes a wearable computer and video camera system that uses computer vision to identify uncommon interest points in geological imagery in real-time. This involves image processing and analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The system is also wearable and mobile, which suggests robotics (cs.RO) as another likely sub-category. The system uses machine learning algorithms to identify interesting features, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions a comparison of the system's results with those of a human geologist, which suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with geological structures and their significance, which falls under graphics (cs.GR).
